<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/46667560-robert-irish"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1493082399i/46667560._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/46667560-robert-irish">Robert Irish</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I&apos;m not sure how this book has much to offer with the racial tension in America. Certainly, it speaks of the African American distrust of the White, a<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I'm not sure how this book has much to offer with the racial tension in America. Certainly, it speaks of the African American distrust of the White, and justifies it pretty well, but that's not what's central here. The central them focuses on the internal workings of the Black community in its relationship to faith in God and each other. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
