<div id="review_1996743457" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1996743457" />
    <a title="Faith" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17430801-faith"><img alt="Faith" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1372868249p2/17430801.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1996743457?book_show_action=true">May 13, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Faith" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Faith" href="/user/show/17430801-faith">Faith</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/18920654-go-tell-it-on-the-mountain">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17430801-faith?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17430801-faith?shelf=overdrive">overdrive</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1996743457" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7557912982089435097">I don&apos;t know why I hadn&apos;t read James Baldwin before, but this year I am trying to rectify that lapse. This is a brilliant, character-driven book, with beautiful use of language. A large part of the book is the coming of age of 14 year old John, who is a surrogate for the author. Although I am not at all religious, I was pulled in by how the family members depicted in this book relied upon and wrestled with their faith in the light of painful experiences, including racism, death, hypocrisy, aband</span>
  <span id="freeText7557912982089435097" style="display:none">I don't know why I hadn't read James Baldwin before, but this year I am trying to rectify that lapse. This is a brilliant, character-driven book, with beautiful use of language. A large part of the book is the coming of age of 14 year old John, who is a surrogate for the author. Although I am not at all religious, I was pulled in by how the family members depicted in this book relied upon and wrestled with their faith in the light of painful experiences, including racism, death, hypocrisy, abandonment, various temptations and abuse. Reading this was a wonderful experience. Adam Lazarre-White was an excellent narrator of the audiobook.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7557912982089435097" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


